relationships.description: Control system contains and manages the pump control unit.
Pump control unit manages multiple pumps.
Control system monitors liquid levels with a level sensor.
Control system monitors gas levels with a gas sensor.
Control system integrates an alarm system for safety alerts.
Control system provides a display panel for system monitoring.
Control system contains an operational data recorder.
Pump control unit interfaces with the ventilation fan for methane mitigation.
Gas sensor readings trigger ventilation fan activation.
Pump anomalies can trigger the alarm system.
LevelSensor extends the generic Sensor class.
GasSensor extends the generic Sensor class.

domain_model.plantuml:
@startuml

class WetWellControlSystem {
  - operationMode : OperationMode
  - alarmState : boolean
  + monitorConditions() : void
  + switchToAutomaticMode() : void
  + switchToManualMode() : void
  + triggerAlarm(alarmType : AlarmType) : void
  + overrideOperation() : void
}

class PumpControlUnit {
  - operationMode : String
  - leadDepth : Double
  - lagDepth : Double
  - highDepth : Double
  - highMethaneVolume : Double
  + startPump(pumpId : String) : void
  + stopPump(pumpId : String) : void
  + equalizePumpRunTime() : void
  + monitorPumps() : void
  + controlOperations() : void
  + handlePumpFailure(pumpId : String, failureType : FailureType) : void
}

class Pump {
  - pumpId : String
  - isRunning : boolean
  - isAvailable : boolean
  - runTime : Double
  - moistureDetected : boolean
  - temperatureTooHigh : boolean
  - sealLeakDetected : boolean
  + start() : void
  + stop() : void
  + updateStatus() : void
}

class Sensor {
  - sensorId : String
  - sensorType : String
  - currentValue : Double
  - threshold : Double
  + readValue() : Double
  + isThresholdExceeded() : Boolean
}

class LevelSensor {
  - sensorId : String
  - currentDepth : Double
  - leadDepth : Double
  - lagDepth : Double
  - highDepth : Double
  + getCurrentDepth() : Double
}

class GasSensor {
  - sensorId : String
  - methaneLevel : Double
  - highMethaneLevel : Double
  - maxMethaneLevel : Double
  + getMethaneLevel() : Double
}

class VentilationFan {
  - isOn : boolean
  + turnOn() : void
  + turnOff() : void
}

class AlarmSystem {
  - activeAlarms : Set<AlarmType>
  + activateAlarm(alarmType : AlarmType) : void
  + deactivateAlarm(alarmType : AlarmType) : void
  + soundBuzzer() : void
  + enableIndicatorLights() : void
}

class DisplayPanel {
  - digitalDepth : Double
  - indicatorLights : Map<String, Boolean>
  + updateDisplay(data : Map) : void
  + showHistoricalData() : void
}

class OperationalDataRecorder {
  - realTimeData : Map<String, Object>
  - historicalData : List<Map<String, Object>>
  + recordData() : void
  + retrieveHistoricalData(timeRange : TimeRange) : List<Map<String, Object>>
}

WetWellControlSystem *-- PumpControlUnit : manages
PumpControlUnit *-- "1..*" Pump : controls
WetWellControlSystem *-- LevelSensor : monitors
WetWellControlSystem *-- GasSensor : monitors
WetWellControlSystem *-- AlarmSystem : alerts
WetWellControlSystem *-- DisplayPanel : displays
WetWellControlSystem *-- OperationalDataRecorder : records
PumpControlUnit --> VentilationFan : interfaces
GasSensor --> VentilationFan : triggers
Pump --> AlarmSystem : alerts
LevelSensor --|> Sensor : extends
GasSensor --|> Sensor : extends

@enduml

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.

issues.description: The term 'hazards' is vague and does not specify which risks (e.g. overflow, gas exposure, pump failure) must be mitigated. The requirement should detail specific hazards and map them to relevant system components.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the hazards (e.g., overflow, gas exposure, pump failure) and link each to components such as AlarmSystem and sensor thresholds.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of liquid in the wet well.

issues.description: The term 'reporting' is vague – it is not clear whether it means logging, alerting, or displaying the measurement.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the reporting mechanism (e.g., assert that LevelSensor readings are displayed on the DisplayPanel and recorded by an OperationalDataRecorder).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of hazardous methane gas.

issues.description: The threshold for what constitutes 'hazardous' methane gas is not defined and the reporting method is not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Define explicit threshold values (using, for example, GasSensor.highMethaneLevel) and clarify how the reading is reported or acted upon.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump and whether it is currently running or not.

issues.description: Uncertainty exists regarding whether the WetWellControlSystem or the PumpControlUnit is responsible for pump status monitoring.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the responsibility by specifying that the PumpControlUnit (or a dedicated pump management component) monitors and reports pump status.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.

issues.description: It is not specified what conditions trigger the alarm or which component activates the visual versus audible elements.
issues.suggested_fix: Detail the hazardous conditions and assign alarm activation to the AlarmSystem (e.g., using methods like soundBuzzer and enableIndicatorLights).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on or off in a timely fashion depending on the level of liquid within the wet well.

issues.description: It is not clear whether the WetWellControlSystem or the PumpControlUnit is responsible for pump switching.
issues.suggested_fix: Assign the responsibility explicitly to the PumpControlUnit and ensure that the level sensor thresholds are tied to pump activation.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching ventilation fans on or off in a timely fashion depending on the concentration of hazardous gas within the wet well.

issues.description: The domain model lacks an explicit method to control ventilation fans centrally; instead, control is implied via GasSensor and its association with PumpControlUnit.
issues.suggested_fix: Either add an explicit ventilation fan control method or reassign the responsibility to the GasSensor trigger logic.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify what 'automated operation' entails or how it differs from other modes.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify that automated operation includes controlling pumps and ventilation based on sensor readings without human intervention.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.

issues.description: The term 'observational operation' is not defined and is not represented in the domain model.
issues.suggested_fix: Define 'observational operation' clearly and ensure it is included in the OperationMode enumeration.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: The conditions differentiating 'running over' from 'running dry' are not defined in terms of water level thresholds.
issues.suggested_fix: Define both high water level and low water level thresholds (or introduce a low-level attribute) to determine pump start/stop conditions.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the environmental conditions within the wet well.

issues.description: Only liquid level and gas sensors are modeled; additional environmental conditions such as temperature or humidity are not represented.
issues.suggested_fix: Extend the domain model to include additional sensors (e.g., TemperatureSensor or HumiditySensor) or adjust the requirement accordingly.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature.

issues.description: This requirement duplicates the functionality already described in REQ-005.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-005 and clearly specify that the AlarmSystem is responsible for both visual and audible alarms.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site.

issues.description: This requirement duplicates manual override functionality mentioned elsewhere.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge this requirement with the corresponding manual override requirement to avoid redundancy.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site.

issues.description: This requirement duplicates REQ-008. The automated operation functionality should be merged and clarified.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove or merge with REQ-008 and clarify operational mode details.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the submersible pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: There is an inconsistency between this requirement and REQ-011 regarding which component is responsible for pump control.
issues.suggested_fix: Clearly assign pump start/stop control to a single component, preferably the PumpControlUnit.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the ventilation fans in the wet well to prevent hazardous levels of methane.

issues.description: The domain model lacks an explicit control method in PumpControlUnit for the ventilation fans.
issues.suggested_fix: Either extend PumpControlUnit with a method to control the VentilationFan or reassign the ventillation control to the GasSensor trigger.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The introduction of methane into the wet well shall cause the ventilation fan to turn on.

issues.description: No specific threshold or sensor reading is defined for triggering the fan.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the methane concentration threshold (using GasSensor attributes) that will trigger the ventilation fan.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: If a pump motor is not available to run and a request has been made for the pump motor to start, an alternative motor shall be started in its place.

issues.description: There is no mechanism or method in the domain model to support selecting an alternative pump if one is unavailable.
issues.suggested_fix: Extend PumpControlUnit with logic or add a method (e.g. 'selectAlternativePump()') to select and start an alternative pump.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: An alarm state shall be set when the high water level is reached.

issues.description: It is not specified which sensor or threshold defines 'high water level' and this requirement appears to duplicate REQ-047.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-047 and specify that when the LevelSensor detects a depth equal to or exceeding its highDepth value, the AlarmSystem is activated.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: An alarm state shall be set when the high methane level is reached.

issues.description: It is unclear whether 'high methane level' corresponds to GasSensor.highMethaneLevel or a maximum threshold.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the threshold measurement (e.g., use GasSensor.highMethaneLevel) and ensure consistency with REQ-049.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The starting and stopping of the pump motors shall be done in manner that equalizes the run times on the motors.

issues.description: This requirement appears to duplicate similar functionality specified elsewhere (e.g. REQ-018).
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with the corresponding requirement to avoid redundancy.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Level switches shall be used to indicate when pump motors should be started.

issues.description: The domain model uses 'LevelSensor' rather than 'level switches'.
issues.suggested_fix: Replace 'level switches' with 'level sensors' to align with the domain model terminology.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be notified if excess moisture is detected in a pump motor.

issues.description: The notification mechanism from the pump to the PumpControlUnit is not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Define a communication or event mechanism by which PumpControlUnit receives pump status updates.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be notified if a pump motor overheats and shall shut down the overheated motor.

issues.description: The notification mechanism and its integration with pump shutdown (e.g., via handlePumpFailure) is not clearly defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the event-driven update process so that the PumpControlUnit can respond when an overheat is detected.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for monitoring the pumping site.

issues.description: It is unclear whether monitoring includes only the pumps or also other site conditions.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that the PumpControlUnit is responsible only for pump-related monitoring while the WetWellControlSystem or additional sensors handle other site conditions.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for recording real time and historical operational parameters.

issues.description: Recording is modeled in the OperationalDataRecorder, not in PumpControlUnit.
issues.suggested_fix: Reassign the recording functionality to the OperationalDataRecorder or update the requirement accordingly.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for providing the alarm feature.

issues.description: Alarm functionality is defined in the domain model under AlarmSystem, not within PumpControlUnit.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove alarm responsibilities from the PumpControlUnit requirement and assign them to the AlarmSystem.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: There shall be an automatic and manual mode for the pump control unit.

issues.description: PumpControlUnit’s operationMode is defined as a String while WetWellControlSystem uses an OperationMode enumeration that includes an observational mode.
issues.suggested_fix: Align the operational mode definitions across components by using a common OperationMode enumeration (with AUTOMATIC, MANUAL, OBSERVATIONAL).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Each pumping station shall either be in automatic mode or manual mode.

issues.description: This requirement excludes the observational mode specified elsewhere, leading to a conflict.
issues.suggested_fix: Update the requirement to include automatic, manual, and observational modes, or reconcile the operating mode definitions across the system.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect occurrence of a pump motor seal leak. If a leak has been detected, both an audible and visible alarm should be activated.

issues.description: The threshold and sensing mechanism for leak detection are not defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the detection threshold for a seal leak and clearly tie the alarm activation to this condition via the AlarmSystem.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control display panel shall have a digital depth of influent measured in feet.

issues.description: The digitalDepth attribute exists but its unit of measurement is not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Annotate the digitalDepth attribute in DisplayPanel with the unit 'feet'.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for displaying real time and historical operational parameters.

issues.description: Display functionality is already modeled in DisplayPanel and OperationalDataRecorder, not in PumpControlUnit.
issues.suggested_fix: Reassign this requirement to DisplayPanel and/or OperationalDataRecorder.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for pump running state.

issues.description: The mapping between the pump running state and the indicator lights on DisplayPanel is not detailed.
issues.suggested_fix: Detail how the pump running state is conveyed via indicator lights on the DisplayPanel.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for pump seal failure state.

issues.description: There is no clear mapping between pump seal failure detection and indicator light activation.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the relationship between seal failure (e.g., a seal leak) and the corresponding indicator lights on DisplayPanel.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for pump high temperature failure state.

issues.description: The mapping between high temperature failure detection and indicator light activation is not clearly defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Define how the 'temperatureTooHigh' attribute in Pump is linked to an indicator light on DisplayPanel.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for high wet well level alarm state.

issues.description: The domain model does not clearly indicate which indicator light corresponds to the high wet well level alarm state.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify within the DisplayPanel design which indicator light is activated when the high wet well level alarm state is set.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be enabled when an alarm state is activated.

issues.description: It is unclear whether the DisplayPanel or the AlarmSystem is responsible for enabling the indicator lights.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the interaction so that the AlarmSystem triggers the DisplayPanel's indicator lights when an alarm is set.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lead pump depth, the float switch shall set a state which causes the first pump to turn on.

issues.description: The requirement uses 'float switch' instead of the domain model term 'LevelSensor' and does not clearly define the ordering of pumps.
issues.suggested_fix: Replace 'float switch' with 'LevelSensor' and clarify the mechanism for selecting the first pump in PumpControlUnit.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lag pump depth, the float switch shall set a state which causes the second pump to turn on.

issues.description: Similar to REQ-045, the use of 'float switch' is inconsistent and the pump ordering is ambiguous.
issues.suggested_fix: Replace 'float switch' with 'LevelSensor' and clearly define the criteria for the lag/second pump designation.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the allowable high liquid depth, the float switch shall set an alarm state.

issues.description: The term 'float switch' is used instead of 'LevelSensor' and this requirement overlaps with REQ-025.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-025 and consistently use 'LevelSensor' to trigger the AlarmSystem when the depth meets or exceeds the highDepth threshold.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the volume of methane is equal to or greater than the high methane volume, the methane sensor shall set a state which causes the ventilation fans to turn on.

issues.description: The term 'volume' is used whereas the domain model uses 'methane level'.
issues.suggested_fix: Use consistent terminology (e.g., 'methane level') and refer to the appropriate GasSensor attribute.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the volume of methane is equal to or greater than the allowable maximum methane volume, the methane sensor shall set an alarm state.

issues.description: There is a terminology mismatch ('volume' vs. 'level'); the domain model defines maxMethaneLevel.
issues.suggested_fix: Replace 'volume' with 'level' to align with the GasSensor's attribute.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Each submersible pump shall be equipped with a moisture sensor that detects the occurrence of an external pump seal failure. Should a seal failure be detected, the pump shall be turned off and alarm state set.

issues.description: It is unclear whether the moisture sensor is solely for moisture detection or is being used to infer a seal leak.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the role of the moisture sensor versus a dedicated seal leak sensor and ensure the appropriate attribute and alarm trigger are used.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: HighDepth represents the depth of liquid that the wet well should be kept below. Should the depth of liquid be equal to or exceed HighDepth, the alarm state is set.

issues.description: The mechanism for monitoring via LevelSensor is not explicitly indicated.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that LevelSensor monitors the depth and triggers the AlarmSystem when HighDepth is reached.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System constraints include the following items: Regulatory agencies including but not limited to the EPA and DEP, Hardware limitations, Interfaces to other applications, Security considerations, Safety considerations.

issues.description: This statement is very general and does not specify actual constraints or their impact on the system.
issues.suggested_fix: Break down the constraints into specific, testable requirements or reference a detailed non-functional requirements document.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for unauthorized access detection and response
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall detect unauthorized physical or electronic access to the system, immediately trigger an alarm, log the event with detailed information, and notify designated security personnel.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ensuring detection and prompt response to unauthorized access is critical to safeguard both personnel and infrastructure.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for role-based user authentication, authorization, and audit logging for critical functions
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall implement role-based user authentication and access control for all sensitive operations, logging every access attempt and manual override with user credentials, timestamps, and action details.
missing_requirements.rationale: Strong access control and comprehensive audit logs prevent unauthorized use and support compliance with security regulations.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data backup and recovery management
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The OperationalDataRecorder shall perform automatic backups of all operational and historical data at configurable intervals and provide procedures for data recovery in case of system failure.
missing_requirements.rationale: Data integrity and availability are essential for operational continuity and regulatory compliance.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for secure remote monitoring, control, and override capabilities
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall provide secure capabilities for remote monitoring, control, and override, allowing authorized personnel to view system status, historical data, and perform critical control operations remotely.
missing_requirements.rationale: Remote access is necessary for timely interventions and managing operations from off-site locations.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system performance metrics and reporting
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall monitor and record performance metrics, including response times, sensor accuracy, system uptime, pump runtime, and alarm frequency, and generate periodic reports for maintenance and regulatory purposes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Performance metrics are vital for ensuring safety, proactive maintenance, and regulatory compliance.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for handling power failures and backup power integration
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall detect power failures and automatically transition to backup power systems, ensuring continuous operation of critical functions and logging all power transition events.
missing_requirements.rationale: Seamless power backup integration is crucial for maintaining system safety during outages.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system initialization, self-test, and shutdown procedures
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall perform a comprehensive initialization process at startup—including sensor calibration, pump status verification, and self-testing—and execute safe shutdown procedures that transition the system to a secure state while logging all events.
missing_requirements.rationale: Structured startup and shutdown procedures ensure all components operate correctly and safely from system boot to shutdown.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for a dedicated maintenance mode and diagnostic interface
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall provide a dedicated maintenance mode that allows authorized personnel to perform diagnostics, calibration, and component servicing without disrupting normal operations, including access to system logs.
missing_requirements.rationale: A dedicated maintenance mode facilitates troubleshooting and routine upkeep while ensuring operational safety.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for standardized interfacing with external systems
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall implement standardized and secure communication interfaces for integration with external systems such as the Sewage Grinder Unit, Valve Vault, Alarm Display Panel, Power Backup System, and Remote Override Control. The system must handle communication failures gracefully by triggering alarms and defaulting to safe operations.
missing_requirements.rationale: Reliable and standardized interfaces are essential for seamless integration and coordinated operation among interdependent systems.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for comprehensive logging, audit trails, and data retention policies
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall maintain detailed logs of all events, user actions, alarms, and operational changes with secure audit trails and configurable data retention and archival policies to support regulatory audits and incident investigations.
missing_requirements.rationale: Robust logging and data retention are vital for troubleshooting, compliance, and maintaining operational transparency.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall be designed to scale and support additional pumps and components without performance degradation, with explicit support for up to 8 pumps.
missing_requirements.rationale: Scalability ensures the system can expand to meet future operational demands.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for rapid system response times to critical conditions
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall respond to critical conditions, such as high methane or water levels, within 500 milliseconds of detection and initiate safety measures within 1 second.
missing_requirements.rationale: Timely responses to hazardous conditions are essential to prevent accidents and ensure system safety.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for sensor failure handling, calibration, and maintenance alerts
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall detect sensor failures, inaccurate readings, and calibration drifts for all sensors (e.g., LevelSensor, GasSensor), trigger appropriate alarms, perform periodic self-tests and calibrations, and alert maintenance personnel when sensor servicing is required.
missing_requirements.rationale: Accurate sensor data is critical for safe operation, making effective sensor monitoring and maintenance imperative.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for regulatory compliance reporting
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall generate detailed compliance reports—including operational data, incident logs, and environmental metrics—in formats approved by regulatory agencies such as the EPA and DEP.
missing_requirements.rationale: Compliance reporting is necessary to meet legal and regulatory obligations and to maintain accountability.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for an acknowledgment and reset mechanism for alarms
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall require that active alarms be explicitly acknowledged by an authorized operator before they can be reset, ensuring that hazardous conditions are fully resolved prior to clearance.
missing_requirements.rationale: This mechanism prevents premature dismissal of alarms, ensuring that all critical hazards are properly addressed.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for configurable sensor thresholds and calibration settings
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall offer a secure interface for authorized personnel to configure and adjust sensor threshold values and calibration settings, with all changes automatically recorded in an audit log.
missing_requirements.rationale: Configurable thresholds allow the system to adapt to varying operational conditions and ensure safe, accurate monitoring.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for defined sensor update frequency
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall update sensor readings at a minimum frequency of once per second, with the ability to accelerate update rates during critical conditions to ensure immediate detection of hazards.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular sensor updates are essential for real-time monitoring and effective hazard detection.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for pump failure escalation procedures
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: If all pumps fail or become unavailable, the system shall escalate the alarm to notify emergency responders and activate contingency measures, such as diverting flow to backup systems.
missing_requirements.rationale: Comprehensive escalation procedures are vital to prevent hazardous overflows and ensure emergency responses are initiated promptly.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for periodic system self-diagnostics
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall perform periodic self-diagnostics to verify the integrity of sensors, pumps, alarms, and communication links, logging any detected faults for further analysis.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular self-diagnostics help in early detection of potential failures, ensuring sustained system reliability.

domain_model_issues.description: The class does not have a method to handle switching to observational mode as required by REQ-010.
PumpControlUnit uses a String for operationMode while WetWellControlSystem uses an OperationMode type.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change the type of operationMode in PumpControlUnit to the common OperationMode enumeration.

domain_model_issues.description: OperationMode is referenced as a type but is not defined; it should include modes such as AUTOMATIC, MANUAL, and OBSERVATIONAL.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an enumeration for OperationMode with the required mode values.

domain_model_issues.description: AlarmType is referenced but not defined in the domain model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an enumeration for AlarmType with appropriate values (e.g., HIGH_WATER, HIGH_METHANE, PUMP_FAILURE).

domain_model_issues.description: FailureType is referenced in PumpControlUnit.handlePumpFailure() but not defined.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an enumeration for FailureType with values such as MOISTURE_DETECTED, OVERHEATING, SEAL_LEAK.

domain_model_issues.description: TimeRange is referenced in OperationalDataRecorder.retrieveHistoricalData() but is not defined.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a TimeRange class with attributes for start and end times.

domain_model_issues.description: There is no mechanism for handling pump unavailability as required by REQ-024.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a method 'selectAlternativePump()' or appropriate failover logic in PumpControlUnit.

domain_model_issues.description: AlarmSystem lacks a method to notify operators when an alarm is activated.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a method 'notifyOperators(AlarmType alarmType)' to AlarmSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: There is no direct association between LevelSensor and PumpControlUnit, despite requirements indicating pump activation based on level readings.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an association between LevelSensor and PumpControlUnit in the domain model.

domain_model_issues.description: There is no direct association between GasSensor and PumpControlUnit needed for controlling ventilation fans based on methane levels.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an association between GasSensor and PumpControlUnit.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiple requirements refer to 'float switch' for depth measurement while the domain model uses 'LevelSensor'.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Clarify in the domain model that LevelSensor serves as the float switch or update the requirements accordingly.

domain_model_issues.description: The domain model currently includes only LevelSensor and GasSensor, although requirements indicate the need for monitoring additional environmental conditions.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Extend the domain model to include additional sensor classes (e.g., TemperatureSensor, HumiditySensor) or adjust the requirements.

domain_model_issues.description: There is a mismatch between recording responsibilities assigned to PumpControlUnit in some requirements and the presence of OperationalDataRecorder in the domain model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Clarify and reassign the data recording functionality solely to OperationalDataRecorder.

domain_model_issues.description: The digitalDepth attribute does not specify its unit of measurement, though it is required to be in feet per REQ-037.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Annotate the digitalDepth attribute with the unit 'feet' in the domain model description.

domain_model_issues.description: Non-functional constraints mentioned in REQ-054 are not represented within the domain model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Extend the domain model to include representations for these constraints or document them in a supplemental requirements specification.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation by implementing fail-safe mechanisms, alarm systems, and automatic shutdowns. Compliance shall be verified through safety audits and certification.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Without specific criteria or measurable performance metrics the safety requirement remains vague. Clarifying what constitutes 'hazards' and how safety is ensured makes it testable and implementable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of liquid in the wet well.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall monitor the wet well liquid level at a defined interval (e.g., every 5 seconds) and report the measured values using a standardized format, including triggering alerts when levels exceed preset thresholds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how accurately the liquid level should be measured, how frequently it should be reported, or where/how it should be reported.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of hazardous methane gas.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring the level of hazardous methane gas in parts per million (ppm) with an accuracy of ±5% and reporting this data to the display panel in real-time with updates at least every 5 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify the units of measurement, accuracy requirements, reporting frequency, or where/how the gas levels should be reported.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump and whether it is currently running or not.
missing_elements: Definition of all possible pump states (e.g., failed, standby)
Reporting destination (e.g., display panel or log)
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump (running, stopped, failed, or unavailable) via the display panel with status updates occurring at least every 3 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how the pump states should be reported, how frequently updates should occur, or what pump states beyond running/not running should be monitored.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.
missing_elements: Specific alarm characteristics (e.g., sound pattern, light color)
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual indicator light and audible buzzer alarm when a hazardous condition exists, including but not limited to high liquid level, high methane concentration, pump failure, or seal leak. The alarm shall remain active until manually acknowledged by an operator or until the hazardous condition is resolved.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't define what constitutes a hazardous condition, what type of visual and audible alarms should be activated, or how the alarms are reset.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on or off in a timely fashion depending on the level of liquid within the wet well.
missing_elements: Defined liquid level thresholds (e.g., leadDepth, lagDepth)
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on when the liquid level reaches or exceeds the lead pump depth (for first pump) or lag pump depth (for second pump), and off when the liquid level falls below the minimum operational depth. The system shall respond to level changes within 2 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement uses the vague term 'timely fashion' without specifying response times, and doesn't define the liquid level thresholds that should trigger pump activation or deactivation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching ventilation fans on or off in a timely fashion depending on the concentration of hazardous gas within the wet well.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall be responsible for switching ventilation fans on when methane concentration reaches or exceeds the high methane volume threshold and off when the concentration falls below the safe threshold level. The system shall respond to concentration changes within 2 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement uses the vague term 'timely fashion' without specifying response times, and doesn't define the gas concentration thresholds that should trigger fan activation or deactivation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation that monitors liquid levels and gas concentrations, controls pumps and ventilation fans according to predefined thresholds, equalizes pump run times, and activates alarms when hazardous conditions are detected, all without requiring operator intervention except for acknowledgment of alarms and manual overrides.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is too vague and doesn't specify what aspects of operation should be automated or how the automated system should function.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation.
missing_elements: Conditions or procedures for manual intervention
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation through the control panel that allows authorized operators to start/stop pumps and ventilation fans individually, while maintaining critical safety interlocks to prevent damage to equipment or creation of hazardous conditions.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how manual override is implemented, what can be overridden, who can perform overrides, or what safety constraints remain in effect during manual operation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.
missing_elements: Details on what data is observed
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation through a display panel that shows real-time status of all pumps, liquid levels, gas concentrations, alarm conditions, and system mode without allowing control inputs, to enable monitoring by maintenance personnel and operators.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't define what 'observational operation' means, what interface should be provided, or what parameters should be observable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.
missing_elements: Defined liquid level thresholds for overflow and dry conditions
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall start the lead pump when liquid level reaches the LeadDepth threshold, start the lag pump when liquid level reaches the LagDepth threshold to prevent overflow, and stop the pumps when the liquid level drops to the MinimumOperationalDepth to prevent the wet well from running dry. Pumps shall be started with at least a 5-second delay between them.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify the exact level thresholds that should trigger pump activation or deactivation, how pumps should be sequenced, or timing requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running by monitoring electrical current draw and pump feedback signals, updating status at least every second, and detecting run state discrepancies that might indicate pump or sensor failure.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how the system should track motor status, how frequently status should be updated, or how to handle discrepancies between commanded and actual states.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the environmental conditions within the wet well.
missing_elements: Specific environmental parameters (e.g., temperature, humidity, gas levels)
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall monitor the environmental conditions within the wet well, including liquid level, methane concentration, temperature, and humidity, at a minimum frequency of once per second, comparing readings against defined thresholds and initiating appropriate actions when thresholds are exceeded.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify which environmental conditions should be monitored, how frequently they should be monitored, what thresholds apply, or what actions should be taken based on the monitoring.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the physical condition of each pump for the existence of moisture and excessive temperatures.
missing_elements: Defined thresholds for moisture and temperature
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall monitor the physical condition of each pump for the existence of moisture (any detection above sensor threshold) and excessive temperatures (above 80°C) at least once every 10 seconds, and shall shut down affected pumps and trigger alarms when these conditions are detected.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what constitutes excessive temperature, what moisture threshold is problematic, how frequently monitoring should occur, or what actions should be taken when problems are detected.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature with visual indicator lights and audible buzzer that activates for high liquid level, high methane concentration, pump failure, seal leaks, and excessive temperature conditions. Alarms shall remain active until acknowledged by an operator or until the triggering condition is resolved.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is too vague and doesn't specify what types of alarms should be provided, what conditions should trigger alarms, how alarms should notify operators, or how alarms are reset.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site.
missing_elements: Conditions under which override is permitted
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site through a secured control panel that allows authorized operators to individually control pumps, ventilation fans, and reset alarms, while maintaining critical safety interlocks to prevent equipment damage or hazardous conditions.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how manual override is implemented, what can be overridden, who can perform overrides, or what safety constraints remain in effect during manual operation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site that monitors liquid levels and gas concentrations, controls pumps and ventilation fans according to predefined thresholds, equalizes pump run times, and activates alarms when hazardous conditions are detected, all without requiring operator intervention except for acknowledgment of alarms and manual overrides.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is too vague and doesn't specify what aspects of operation should be automated or how the automated system should function. This is also redundant with REQ-008.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall equalize the run time between the pumps.
missing_elements: Definition of acceptable run time variance
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall equalize the run time between the pumps by alternating the lead pump designation after each pumping cycle, with the goal of maintaining run time differences of less than 10% between any two pumps over a 30-day period.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how run time should be equalized, what degree of equalization is acceptable, or how frequently adjustments should be made to maintain equalization.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the submersible pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.
missing_elements: Defined thresholds for starting and stopping
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall start the lead pump when liquid level reaches the LeadDepth threshold, start the lag pump when liquid level reaches the LagDepth threshold to prevent overflow, and stop the pumps when the liquid level drops to the MinimumOperationalDepth to prevent the wet well from running dry. Pumps shall be started with at least a 5-second delay between them.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify the exact level thresholds that should trigger pump activation or deactivation, how pumps should be sequenced, or timing requirements. This is also redundant with REQ-011.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the ventilation fans in the wet well to prevent hazardous levels of methane.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall start the ventilation fans in the wet well within 2 seconds when methane concentration reaches or exceeds the high methane volume threshold (defined as [specific value] ppm) to prevent hazardous levels of methane.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what methane concentration triggers fan activation, how quickly fans should be activated, or how to verify that fans are operating correctly.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The introduction of methane into the wet well shall cause the ventilation fan to turn on.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The detection of methane at or above the high methane volume threshold (defined as [specific value] ppm) by the gas sensor in the wet well shall cause the ventilation fan to turn on within 2 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what concentration of methane should trigger fan activation, how quickly the fan should respond, or how methane is detected.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running by monitoring electrical current draw and pump feedback signals, updating status at least every second, and detecting run state discrepancies that might indicate pump or sensor failure.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how the system should track motor status, how frequently status should be updated, or how to handle discrepancies between commanded and actual states. This is redundant with REQ-012.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is available to run.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is available to run based on maintenance status, fault conditions (moisture, temperature, seal leaks), and manual override settings, updating availability status at least every 5 seconds and displaying current status on the control panel.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what criteria determine if a motor is available, how frequently availability status should be updated, or how availability information should be communicated.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: If a pump motor is not available to run and a request has been made for the pump motor to start, an alternative motor shall be started in its place.
missing_elements: Definition and selection criteria for alternative motor
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: If a pump motor is not available to run and a request has been made for the pump motor to start, an alternative motor shall be started in its place within 3 seconds, selecting the pump with the lowest run time from available pumps. If no alternative pump is available, an alarm shall be activated.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how to select which alternative motor to use, whether to notify operators of the substitution, or what to do if no alternative is available.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: An alarm state shall be set when the high water level is reached.
missing_elements: Numerical threshold definition for high water level
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: An alarm state shall be set when the high water level (defined as the HighDepth threshold) is reached, activating both visual indicator lights and audible buzzer, and triggering emergency protocols including activating all available pumps.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't define what constitutes the high water level, what type of alarm should be activated, or what additional actions should be taken when this condition occurs.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: An alarm state shall be set when the high methane level is reached.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: An alarm state shall be set when the high methane level (defined as the maximum methane volume threshold) is reached, activating both visual indicator lights and audible buzzer, and triggering emergency protocols including maximum ventilation.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't define what constitutes the high methane level, what type of alarm should be activated, or what additional actions should be taken when this condition occurs.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The starting and stopping of the pump motors shall be done in a manner that equalizes the run times on the motors.
missing_elements: Definition of acceptable run time variance
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The starting and stopping of the pump motors shall be done in a manner that equalizes the run times on the motors by alternating the lead pump designation after each pumping cycle, with the goal of maintaining run time differences of less than 10% between any two pumps over a 30-day period.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how run time should be equalized, what degree of equalization is acceptable, or how frequently adjustments should be made to maintain equalization. This is redundant with REQ-018.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Level switches shall be used to indicate when pump motors should be started.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Float-type level switches installed at the LeadDepth and LagDepth positions within the wet well shall be used to indicate when pump motors should be started, with redundant sensors providing fault tolerance in case of primary sensor failure.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what type of level switches should be used, where they should be located, what threshold values apply, or how to ensure reliability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be notified if excess moisture is detected in a pump motor.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall be notified within 1 second if excess moisture is detected in a pump motor by the moisture sensor, and shall automatically shut down the affected pump, mark it as unavailable, and activate the moisture alarm indicator.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what constitutes excess moisture, how notification should occur, or what actions should be taken in response to the notification.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be notified if a pump motor overheats and shall shut down the overheated motor.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall be notified within 1 second if a pump motor temperature exceeds 80°C as detected by the temperature sensor, and shall immediately shut down the overheated motor and activate the temperature alarm indicator.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what temperature constitutes overheating or how the notification should occur.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for monitoring the pumping site.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall be responsible for monitoring the pumping site, including liquid levels, methane concentration, pump status, temperature, and moisture conditions, at least once per second, and shall initiate appropriate control actions and alarms based on monitored values.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is too vague and doesn't specify what aspects of the pumping site should be monitored, how frequently monitoring should occur, or what actions should be taken based on monitoring results.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for recording real time and historical operational parameters.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall be responsible for recording real-time and historical operational parameters including liquid levels, methane concentrations, pump run times, alarm events, and system mode changes, at intervals of at least once per minute, retaining data for a minimum of 90 days, and providing access through the display panel interface.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify which operational parameters should be recorded, how frequently they should be recorded, how long data should be retained, or how the data can be accessed.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for providing the alarm feature.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall be responsible for providing the alarm feature with visual indicator lights and audible buzzer that activates for high liquid level, high methane concentration, pump failure, seal leaks, and excessive temperature conditions. Alarms shall remain active until acknowledged by an operator or until the triggering condition is resolved.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is too vague and doesn't specify what types of alarms should be provided, what conditions should trigger alarms, how alarms should notify operators, or how alarms are reset. This is redundant with REQ-015.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: There shall be an automatic and manual mode for the pump control unit.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: There shall be an automatic and manual mode for the pump control unit, selectable via a keyed switch on the control panel. In automatic mode, pumps and ventilation are controlled based on sensor readings. In manual mode, operators can directly control individual pumps and ventilation. The system shall default to automatic mode upon startup.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how to switch between modes, how the system behaves in each mode, or what the default mode should be.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Each pumping station shall either be in automatic mode or manual mode.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Each pumping station shall either be in automatic mode or manual mode, as selected by a keyed switch on the control panel, with the current mode clearly indicated by dedicated indicator lights. The system shall default to automatic mode upon startup.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how to switch between modes, how to indicate the current mode, or what the default mode should be. This is also partially redundant with REQ-034.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor and detect occurrence of a pump motor seal leak. If a leak has been detected, both an audible and visible alarm should be activated.
missing_elements: Consistency in modal language ('shall' instead of 'should')
Quantitative criteria or sensor thresholds for leak detection
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The system shall monitor and detect occurrence of a pump motor seal leak using dedicated moisture sensors. If a leak has been detected, both an audible buzzer and visible indicator light alarm shall be activated within 2 seconds, and the affected pump shall be automatically shut down and marked as unavailable.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how seal leaks should be detected, how quickly alarms should be activated, or what additional actions should be taken beyond activating alarms.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control display panel shall have a digital depth of influent measured in feet.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control display panel shall have a digital depth indicator showing the current level of influent measured in feet with a precision of 0.1 feet, updating at least once per second, and capable of displaying the full range from empty (0 feet) to maximum capacity.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify the precision of the digital display, how frequently it should update, or what range of values it should be able to display.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for displaying real time and historical operational parameters.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The pump control unit shall be responsible for displaying real-time operational parameters (liquid level, methane concentration, pump status, alarms) on the main screen updating every second, and historical operational parameters (trends, run times, alarm history) accessible through menu options covering at least the past 30 days of operation.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify which operational parameters should be displayed, how they should be displayed, what time range of historical data should be available, or how frequently the display should update.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for pump running state.
missing_elements: Details on light colors or patterns
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Indicator lights with predefined colors (e.g., green for running) shall be provided on the control panel to denote the running state of each pump, activating immediately when a pump is running and deactivating when it is not.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what color the indicator lights should be, where they should be located, or exactly how they should behave.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for pump seal failure state.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Red indicator lights shall be provided on the control panel for each pump's seal failure state, illuminating when a seal leak is detected in the corresponding pump and remaining lit until the condition is resolved and manually reset.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what color the indicator lights should be, where they should be located, or exactly how they should behave.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for pump high temperature failure state.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Red indicator lights shall be provided on the control panel for each pump's high temperature failure state, illuminating when the corresponding pump overheats and remaining lit until the condition is resolved and manually reset.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what color the indicator lights should be, where they should be located, or exactly how they should behave.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be provided for high wet well level alarm state.
missing_elements: Definition of high wet well level
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: A red indicator light shall be provided on the control panel for high wet well level alarm state, illuminating when the liquid level reaches or exceeds the HighDepth threshold and remaining lit until the level falls below the threshold.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify what color the indicator light should be, where it should be located, or exactly how it should behave.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Indicator lights shall be enabled when an alarm state is activated.
missing_elements: Mapping between specific alarms and indicator lights
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The corresponding red indicator lights for each alarm condition (high level, high methane, pump failure, seal leak, high temperature) shall be enabled when an alarm state is activated and shall remain lit until the alarm condition is resolved and acknowledged by an operator via the reset button.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify which indicator lights should be enabled for which alarm conditions, how they should behave once enabled, or how they are reset.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: A buzzer shall sound when an alarm state is activated.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: A buzzer producing an 85dB audible alert shall sound continuously when any alarm state is activated and shall continue until silenced by an operator pressing the alarm silence button, even if the alarm condition persists.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify the characteristics of the buzzer sound, how long it should sound, or how it can be silenced.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lead pump depth, the float switch shall set a state which causes the first pump to turn on.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lead pump depth, the float switch shall set a state within 1 second which causes the first pump to turn on. If the float switch fails, the system shall use backup level sensor readings to determine pump activation.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement doesn't specify how quickly the state should be set after the depth threshold is reached or how to handle float switch failures.

reasoning.domain_model: The consensus model combines key elements from all three models. The WetWellControlSystem class integrates monitoring, mode switching, and alarm triggering methods from all sources. The PumpControlUnit merges pump management functionalities from Model1 and Model3, while Pump unifies pump attributes using a string identifier. Generic sensor functionality is captured in the Sensor class, with LevelSensor and GasSensor extending it to reconcile differences between LiquidLevelMonitor/MethaneMonitor and LevelSensor/GasSensor. Ventilation is controlled via the VentilationFan, linked to both the PumpControlUnit and GasSensor. AlarmSystem and DisplayPanel merge alerting and UI responsibilities, and OperationalDataRecorder is carried over from Model1. Inheritance and associations were defined to capture relationships present in the source models, resulting in a comprehensive, coherent domain model.
reasoning.analysis: The combined analysis integrates all unique insights from the three source analyses. Duplicate requirement issues were merged by consolidating similar issues (for example, multiple mentions of ambiguous automated operation or conflicting mode definitions were combined into single entries with comprehensive suggested fixes). Missing requirements appearing in all analyses were preserved with identical details, ensuring no unique security, performance, or operational requirements were omitted. Finally, domain model issues from both sources were integrated, with overlapping issues (such as inconsistencies in operation mode definitions, missing associations, and absent enumerated types) merged into unified entries that capture all identified concerns and their suggested fixes.
